b)    Wages shall be paid by the Employer, before quitting
              time. Accompanying each payment of wages shall be a
              statement, in writing, or an electronic statement, except
              where otherwise requested by the employee, which can be
              retained by the employee, setting forth.

i)      The period of time or the work for which the wages
                       are being paid;

ii)      The rate of wages to which the employee is entitled;

iii)     The amount of wages to which the employee is
                       entitled;

iv)      The amount of each deduction from the wages of the
                       employee and the purpose for which each deduction
                       is made;

v)       Any allowance or other payment to which the
                       employee is entitled;

vi)      The amount of vacation pay for which the employee is
                       being credited;
